# Rocket.new — Autonomous Quality Assurance System

> Quality is no longer a manual step. It is an automatic property of every commit.
> Every time you commit code, the system automatically checks it against every rule.
> You do not have to remember to run /review-diff. It runs itself.

---

## SETUP (One command per project)

```bash
sh .cursor/hooks-scripts/install-git-hooks.sh
```

This installs the post-commit review hook. After this, every `git commit` automatically:
1. Scans changed files against all critical rules
2. Reports violations in the terminal immediately
3. Logs everything to `memory-bank/code-review-log.md`

---

## WHAT IT CHECKS ON EVERY COMMIT

| Check | Rule | Severity |
|---|---|---|
| `// ... existing code` in any file | Lazy Delete bug | 🔴 Critical |
| `getSession()` in .ts/.tsx files | Server auth pattern | 🔴 Critical |
| `request.json()` in webhook routes | Stripe signature | 🔴 Critical |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_` on service role key | Secret exposure | 🔴 Critical |
| `middleware.ts` inside `/app/` | Wrong location | 🔴 Critical |
| Unawaited `cookies()` | Next.js 15 | 🟡 Warning |

---

## THE WORKFLOW

```
You accept a Cursor fix
        ↓
git add -A && git commit -m "fix: auth session"
        ↓
post-commit hook fires automatically (< 1 second)
        ↓
Scans every changed file
        ↓
❌ Issues found → reported in terminal instantly
✅ No issues → "AI code review passed" confirmation
        ↓
Everything logged to memory-bank/code-review-log.md
```

---

## READING THE REVIEW LOG

```bash
# See the last 20 review entries
tail -100 memory-bank/code-review-log.md

# See only failed reviews
grep -A5 "REVIEW NEEDED" memory-bank/code-review-log.md

# Count total commits reviewed
grep -c "^## \[" memory-bank/code-review-log.md
```

---

## WHEN THE HOOK FINDS ISSUES

The hook reports issues but does NOT block the commit.
(Blocking commits creates friction — reporting creates awareness.)

When issues are reported:
1. Read the specific violation
2. Run the appropriate fix command (`/fix-auth`, `/debug-error`, etc.)
3. Fix the issue
4. Commit again — the hook will confirm it's clean

---

## EXTENDING THE HOOK

To add a new check to `post-commit-review.sh`:

```bash
# Add after the existing checks, before "Compile all issues"

NEW_PATTERN=$(echo "$CHANGED_FILES" | while read f; do
  if [ -f "$f" ]; then
    if grep -q "YOUR_PATTERN" "$f" 2>/dev/null; then
      echo "❌ YOUR_MESSAGE in $f"
    fi
  fi
done)

# Add to ALL_ISSUES compilation:
[ -n "$NEW_PATTERN" ] && ALL_ISSUES="$ALL_ISSUES\n$NEW_PATTERN"
```

Every time /capture-convention creates a new rule → add it to the hook too.
The QA system should be as current as the rules.

---

## THE THREE-LAYER QUALITY SYSTEM

```
Layer 1 — Pre-change:    /review-diff (manual, before accepting)
Layer 2 — Post-commit:   post-commit hook (automatic, after committing)
Layer 3 — Weekly:        weekly-security-sweep automation (background, scheduled)
```

Together these three layers mean:
- Nothing bad gets accepted without a chance to catch it (/review-diff)
- Nothing bad gets committed without being flagged (post-commit hook)
- Nothing bad accumulates over time without being surfaced (weekly sweep)

**Quality is no longer a decision. It is the default.**
